.:: Puzzle 6x3-Level-8-2::.
The people have 3 different hobbies: card-games, filmmaking, photography
The people have 3 different jobs:  dancer, manager, writer
The people use 3 different means of transport: subway, snowmobile, taxi
There are 3 different nationalities: brazilian, egyptian, italian
3 different pets are kept: bird, fish, goldfish
3 different games are played: billiard, chess, bridge
 1. the person driving the subway is not to the right of the person who's hobby is filmmaking##8
 2. the egyptian is the person playing chess##1
 3. the person who's hobby is filmmaking is the person driving the snowmobile##1
 4. the writer is not to the left of the person who's hobby is filmmaking##8
 5. the italian is on the left or right of the dancer##3
 6. the writer is on the right of the dancer##1
 7. the person playing chess is on the left of the person who's hobby is card-games##1
 8. the owner of the bird is on the far left##1
 9. the egyptian is not the person driving the subway##6
10. the person driving the snowmobile is somewhere to the right of the owner of the bird##5
11. the egyptian is not to the right of the brazilian##8
12. the person playing billiard is somewhere to the left of the person playing chess##5
13. the person playing chess is somewhere between the manager and the owner of the goldfish##7

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |     2      |     3      |
| Hobby         | photography | filmmaking | card-games |
| Job           | manager     | dancer     | writer     |
| Transport   | subway       | snowmobile      | taxi     |
| Nationality   | italian     | egyptian   | brazilian  |
| Pet           | bird        | fish       | goldfish   |
| Game         | billiard  | chess    | bridge     |

